<h3 id="1-which-option-provides-better-cash-flow-for-my-business">1. Which option provides better cash flow for my business?</h3>
<p>Equipment leasing typically provides better short-term cash flow because it requires little to no upfront investment. With 0% deposit options, you can acquire equipment immediately while preserving working capital for other business needs. However, purchasing may provide better long-term cash flow if you can utilize tax depreciation benefits and capture residual equipment value. The best choice depends on your current cash position, business growth plans, and equipment usage intensity.</p>
